      "width": "250px"
    },
    mdxType: "BlogImage"
  }), mdx("p", null, "Finally, I wired and soldered up a board using some remaining perfboard from my house. I assembled the side panels and connected them to the housing with glue.\nI then connected the LEDs to the board, and I was able to test it out. The display you can see on top allows me to add messages to the lamp, which I can change\nusing a web interface I wrote. I then added a power supply and a switch, and I was done!"), mdx(BlogImage, {
    src: props.articleImages[4],
    caption: "Testing the LEDs",
    style: {
      "width": "400px"
    },
    mdxType: "BlogImage"
